APELAFICO integral study

Section 1: data processing WBAT data There is WBAT data at both 70khz CW and 200khz FM (asynchronous pinging). The data are annotated with labeling bottom and surface lines.

For both frequencies, SA (~fish biomass) is exported using a threshold on sv (volume backscattering), meaning all above this treshold is considered fish. Here, the data are exported at thresholds ranging -60dB to -50dB in 1 dB steps.

For the 200khz FM, a dedicated processing is in place to: 1) track the targets with a target detection algorithm, 2) extracts tracks and corresponding frequency spectrum. This is currently work in progress.

CPOD data CPOD data are available alongside all WBAT recordings expect HKZ and HKN data sets. All the data have been processed with click train classification (using CPOD.exe) and further bluzz click classification, using gaussian mixture models.
